item.title: DECCA: Sonia Delaunay Performance 2025
item.dc:creator: 42808013e
item.content:encoded:
What is a Performance in a Museum Context? A performance in a museum is a live, embodied artistic expression that interacts with the space, artworks, and audience. It can involve movement, sound, spoken word, or other forms of artistic expression to create a dialogue between the performers and the exhibited works. Museum performances often encourage active participation, reinterpretation, and a deeper engagement with art beyond passive observation.
Exploring Sonia Delaunay Through Movement In our class on Sonia Delaunay, we transformed her vibrant, dynamic paintings into movement. Inspired by her use of geometric shapes, rhythm, and colour, students translated visual elements into physical gestures, embodying the energy and motion within her works. This process led to a collective choreography, where individual movements merged into a structured performance. Through this experience, students not only deepened their understanding of Delaunay’s artistic language but also explored how abstract art can inspire and be expressed through the body.
item.category: EOILPGC: Inglés a través del arte.
